Reading hundreds of paranormal stories where someone gets saved by a dog, feels safe from unknown dangers in the presence of even a wild dog, gets snapped out of a deadly trance-like terror by a dog, etc. has actually cemented to me the idea that dog is man's best friend.

There are a ton of science-y articles about how dogs are able to tell a seizure is coming to an epileptic an hour in advance, can smell melanoma and tumours forming, etc. It's a creature that more than any other (except arguably the cat) is built to be man's companion and friend.
